This data confirms what sociologists, archaeologists, and historians have ascertained through cultural analysis: human society has passed through three distinct epochs of energy consumption representing fundamentally different modes of social organization. Mass urban industrial society is not a more developed version of previous social forms. It is a **qualitatively different form** requiring orders of magnitude more energy per unit area and generating orders of magnitude more entropy per unit time.

